<p> </p>
<p></p>
<p>April 17, 2020<br><br>Dear HISD Family, </p>
<p>As promised, Hondo ISD wants to make sure you have up-to-date information when it comes to the coronavirus (COVID-19) and its impact on our District. <br></p>
<p>Hondo ISD will comply with the Governor’s resolution closing Texas schools through the end of this school year to help prevent possible exposure to students, staff and the community.</p>
<p>The District will continue to offer instruction to our students and campus principals will inform you as to the details of that situation. Student meals will continue to be served.</p>
<p>This is an evolving situation, and additional information will be coming from TEA this next week. Please watch district and campus websites and Twitter feeds for notices from administration detailing any new developments.<br><br>Sincerely,<br><br>A’Lann Truelock, Ed.D.  <br>Superintendent of Schools</p>
